[1] Costa Rica
Date: Fri, 10 Oct 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: CNNenEspanol.com-Salud; [edited & translated by Maria Jacobs,
ProMED-ESP]
<http://cnnenespanol.com/2003/salud/10/10/costarica.dengue.ap/index.html>


Cases of dengue fever continue to increase in Costa Rica
----------------------------------------------------
According to the most recent report from the ministry of health, 12
885 cases of dengue fever have already been registered in Costa Rica,
and the number continues to increase. Eduardo Lopez, vice minister
for health, commented that 38 of the detected cases correspond to
dengue hemorrhagic fever [DHF]. These numbers are already higher than
those registered for 2002, when 12 251 cases of dengue fever were
recorded, 27 of which were of DHF.

Lopez announced that the country's medical centers receive an average
of 600 new cases each week and that the coastal zones are the most
affected.

The health authorities have expressed their concern that the rainiest
months of the year are still to come.

--
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

