[2] El Salvador
Date: Mon, 13 Oct 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Associated Press; [edited & translated by Maria Jacobs, ProMED-ESP]
<http://www.azcentral.com/spanish/health/articles/health_5058.html >


The number of dengue casualties rises to 6
--------------------------------------------------
Government sources announced that with the deaths of a 6-month-old
girl and a 9-month-old boy, the number of victims of dengue fever in
El Salvador has reached 6.

Herbert Betancourt, minister for health, reported that the children
died in a hospital in the capital, and commented that the last victim
was recorded in March [2003].

Groups of physicians, epidemiologists, and soldiers are carrying out
extensive fumigation campaigns and "home by home" inspections in the
capital, San Salvador, and peripheral areas, where, according to
Betancourt, the largest number of cases (almost 80 percent) is
concentrated. The official also urged the population to collaborate
in the elimination of mosquito breeding sites so that the outbreak
could be controlled.

So far this year [2003], at least 4076 suspected cases of dengue
fever have been registered, among which 1522 cases of classic dengue
fever and 81 cases of DHF have been confirmed.

In 2002, DHF caused the deaths of 9 children and one adult, and more
than 4000 cases of dengue fever were registered.

--
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

